body.description:
First concrete device implementation: Postgres. Serves as the proof-of-concept that BaseDevice works and the design is right.

Proposed shape:
- agent_datacenter/devices/postgres/device.py:
  class PostgresDevice(BaseDevice):
    who_am_i() → {'name': 'postgres', 'version': pg_version(), 'purpose': 'primary relational store'}
    requirements() → {'port': 5432, 'user': env.POSTGRES_USER, 'db': env.POSTGRES_DB}
    capabilities() → {'query': True, 'write': True, 'migrate': True}
    comms() → {'read_write': True, 'push': False, 'pull': True, 'nudge': False}
    interface_version() → INTERFACE_VERSION
    health() → {'connected': bool, 'query_latency_ms': float, 'active_connections': int}
    uptime() → seconds since pg process start (pg_postmaster_start_time)
    startup_errors() → parse pg_log for ERROR lines in last 5min
    logs() → {'path': pg_log_dir, 'format': 'postgresql-%Y-%m-%d.log'}
    update_info() → {'method': 'pg_ctl or Docker', 'current_version': ...}
    where_and_how() → {'socket': '/var/run/postgresql', 'config': pg_hba_conf, 'data_dir': ...}
    Lifecycle methods (restart/block/halt) delegate to shim

Affected files:
- ~/dev/src/agent_datacenter/agent_datacenter/devices/postgres/device.py

Design rules:
- oop-first: PostgresDevice is a class, not a module with functions; delegation pattern to shim
- no-sqlite: PostgresDevice does NOT use sqlite3 for anything

Scope boundary:
IN: full BaseDevice implementation for Postgres; all 16 methods
OUT: pg_ctl/Docker lifecycle (T-adc-postgres-shim), block behavior on dependents (T-adc-postgres-block-clear-error)

Test plan:
- PostgresDevice() instantiates cleanly (all abstract methods implemented)
- health() returns correct shape when Postgres is running
- health() returns {connected: False, ...} when Postgres is not running (no exception raised)
- where_and_how() returns non-None values for socket and data_dir
